# Research Benchmark Pipeline

This directory contains the runnable research project inside the repository.
It packages the benchmark loaders, model/QUBO flow, quantum runner, smoke tests, examples, and checked-in paper artifacts.

## What Is Here

- `src/qobench/`: installable Python package.
- `run_benchmark.py`: wrapper for the classical/model/QUBO CLI.
- `run_hardware_benchmark.py`: wrapper for the hardware/backend CLI.
- `run_simulator_benchmark.py`: wrapper that forces local simulator execution.
- `run_all_algorithms_smoke.py`: short local smoke suite across all supported methods.
- `examples/`: sample inputs and credential templates.
- `research_benchmark/`: checked-in result artifacts used for the paper.
- `all_logs/`: preserved raw logs from longer exploratory sweeps.
- `checkpoints/`: checkpoint JSONs for resumable benchmark batches.

All wrapper scripts now resolve their default paths from the repository layout instead of the current shell directory, so results land in stable locations even if you launch them from a different working directory.

## Install

From the repository root:

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
.venv/bin/python -m pip install --upgrade pip
.venv/bin/python -m pip install -r requirements.txt
.venv/bin/python -m pip install -e research_benchmark
```

## Entry Points

After editable install, these commands are available:

```bash
qobench --help
qobench-hardware --help
qobench-smoke --help
```

You can also use the wrapper scripts directly:

```bash
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_benchmark.py --help
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_hardware_benchmark.py --help
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_simulator_benchmark.py --help
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_all_algorithms_smoke.py --help
```

## Typical Workflows

List dataset instances:

```bash
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_benchmark.py list-instances --problem mis --limit 10
```

Run one model/QUBO benchmark:

```bash
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_benchmark.py \
  run \
  --problem mis \
  --instance Maximum_Independent_Set/mis_benchmark_instances/1tc.8.txt \
  --to-qubo \
  --export-lp
```

Run one local simulator job:

```bash
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_simulator_benchmark.py \
  --problem mkp \
  --instance Multi_Dimension_Knapsack/MKP_Instances/sac94/hp/hp1.dat \
  --method qaoa \
  --shots 128 \
  --maxiter 10
```

Run the multi-method smoke suite:

```bash
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_all_algorithms_smoke.py \
  --problem mis \
  --qpu-id local_qiskit \
  --shots 128 \
  --maxiter 10
```

Run one hardware submission:

```bash
.venv/bin/python research_benchmark/run_hardware_benchmark.py \
  --problem mkp \
  --instance Multi_Dimension_Knapsack/MKP_Instances/sac94/hp/hp1.dat \
  --method cvar_vqe \
  --execution-mode single \
  --qpu-id ibm_quantum \
  --only-qpu ibm_quantum \
  --shots 1000 \
  --maxiter 20
```

## Output Locations

The package uses stable repository-relative defaults:

- Model/QUBO runs: `research_benchmark/runs/`
- Hardware results: `research_benchmark/research_benchmark/results_hardware/`
- Simulator results: `research_benchmark/research_benchmark/results_simulator/`
- Simulator checkpoints: `research_benchmark/research_benchmark/simulator_checkpoints/`
- Batch checkpoints: `research_benchmark/checkpoints/`
- Smoke runs: `research_benchmark/results_hardware_smoke/`

## Notes on Preserved Artifacts

The checked-in outputs are intentional. They are part of the paper companion story and provide traceability for tables, plots, summaries, and queue/runtime logs.

